revision.text:
Shrines dedicated to [[Himegami]] are found throughout Japan. Shrines simply called "Hime Shrine" are often the {{ill|Setsumatsusha|en|Setsumatsusha|qid=Q1071160|lt=Sessha and Massha|1=Setsumatsusha}} (subsidiary shrines) of larger shrines.

* {{ill|Hime Shrine (Nagasaki)|ja|姫神社|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Shrine (Nagasaki)|qq=}}

=== Notable Shrines ===
* {{ill|Hime Shrine (Oyabe City)|ja|比賣神社 (小矢部市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Shrine (Oyabe City)|1=Hime Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q60985334}}
* {{ill|Hime Shrine (Nanto City)|ja|比賣神社 (南砺市)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Shrine (Nanto City)|1=Hime Shrine (Nanto City)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q43594869}}
